Kratko objašnjenje koje napišeš
The application was deployed locally using Podman as a WordPress container, while the database was deployed as a MySQL container. Both containers are connected to the same custom backend network, so the application reaches the database by using the database service name db and internal MySQL port 3306. Only the application port is published to the host on port 8080, while the database is not exposed directly.

The container resource usage was checked with podman stats. Compared to a virtual machine, containers usually use fewer resources because they do not run a full guest operating system and do not have their own kernel. A VM has stronger isolation because it includes a full OS, but it also has higher memory, CPU and disk overhead. In this task the app and database run as containers inside the existing VM, which is lighter and faster than running each component in a separate VM.
